<dl id="n11094c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11094c">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11094c"> 94(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> D Locard / Spilsbury clue of <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">dirt</span></span> dust</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b><mark>Dust as a Clue</mark>.</b> <font color="green">[...]</font> The French authorities have recently announced the use of a vacuum cleaner to draw the dust from the clothing of suspected persons. This method has been, apparently, officially adopted as a method of crime detection, and its success is partly due to the energies of <mark>Dr. Locard</mark> of Lyons, who is establishing a record as a criminologist in France equal to that of Sir Bernard <mark>Spilsbury</mark> in this country. <small> <a name="DM27jun24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DM27jun24"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (27 June 1924) 8/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
